0.5.0
- rebalances, renames and rewordings
- adapt to work in vanilla
- made compatible with Proper Necro

0.2.0 (RC)
- the perk tree splits into two mutually exclusive paths, chosen implicitly by the first
  group perk taken (the closed path is greyed out in the tree):
  - Nature (Supporter): Regrowth, Hatch, Entangling Roots, Greater Beasts
  - Beast (Fighter): Beastform (gate) -> Beast Aura, Beast Rage
  - Venom is ungrouped and adapts to whichever path you commit to
- Beastform: a one-time permanent transformation - physical bonuses, but no heavy shields,
  helmets or armor and no ranged weapons; takes on a beast look when Fantasy Brothers is present
- Beast Aura: your beasts keep to your side and any allied beast near you stands fearless
  and emboldened (absorbs the old Pack Leader)
- Beast Rage: a stacking fury (melee damage, Resolve, Initiative, per-turn healing, less
  Melee Defense) that tears off your shield at its height
- Venom now also rides a Beastform druid's own melee hits
- the summon yields a plain Wolf until level 5, then the full biome variety opens up
- removed Pack Leader (folded into Beast Aura)

0.1.0
- initial version
- Druid background, hireable from the start, with a Summon Beast active
- beasts are chosen by the battlefield: wolves in snow, wolves/spiders on grassland,
  wolves/spiders/young schrats in forests, wolves/hyenas on steppe and hills,
  hyenas/snakes in the desert, spiders/snakes in swamps
- Druid-only perks: Apex Predators, Pack, Regrowth, Entangling Roots, Venom, Pack Leader
- Regrowth heals one ally per turn; only one ally can carry it at a time
- Proper Druid origin
- Russian localization (req Rosetta)
